    {
      "_id": "RGaUdIjwMpgnNYGg",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
      "name": "Pain Starvation",
      "sort": 600000,
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>A specter that goes for more than a month without dealing negative damage to a living humanoid becomes desperate and almost feral. It changes alignment from lawful evil to chaotic evil, loses control of any corrupted thralls it might have, and becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.nlCjDvLMf2EkV2dl]{Quickened}. It can use its additional action only to make vile touch Strikes against humanoid targets. At the end of any turn in which it deals any amount of negative damage to a living humanoid, it reverts to lawful evil and is no longer quickened, but any thralls it lost control of remain free.</p>"
        },
